column1:
Find the complex conjugate of the following: 
2 j ( 3 - j )

In the following MATLAB code, two vectors are assigned complex values, and then a computation is done: 
      x = j*[{a} , {b}]
      y = j*[{c} ; {d}]
      real(x*conj(y))
One is a row vector; the other a column.

What is the value of the variable ans which will hold the value of the unassigned computation, abs(x*y)?
  • The answer turns out to be an integer number.

column1: Match the following values of sines and cosines:

The following signal is a sum of sinusoids that can be simplified and expressed as a single sinusoid of the form: A\cos(\omega t + \varphi), where \varphi is the phase in radians such that - \pi < \varphi \leq\pi. 
3\cos(  999 t - 0.2\pi) + 5\cos( 999 t + 0.6\pi)
Give numerical answers for the amplitude A and phase \varphi in the two boxes.
  • The answer should be numeric, with 3 or more significant digits .
  • Either fixed or exponential notation (e.g. 0.0015 or 1.5e-3) is acceptable.
  • An answer with pi such as 9*pi, will NOT be accepted; a number must be entered.
  • An answer for the phase should lie in the range BETWEEN -\pi and \pi, i.e., (-\pi,\pi].
